accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Original videotapes in box 8 of original accession and boxes 2 and 3 of Accession 2006-M-012 may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright status for collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: AIDS Collection (MS 1834). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged in two series and six additions: I. Countries, 1985-1999. II. International, 1990-1999.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The series is arranged alphabetically by country. Within country, materials are arranged alphabetically by name of organization that produced them. Within organization, materials are arranged alphabetically by title of the printed piece. Materials for which no organization can be determined are located at the end of each country under the heading "unaffiliated." Materials whose country of origin cannot be determined are found at the end of the series.

Original videotape in Box 8 may not be played. Readers may only play use copies. Use copies do not exist, therefore researchers must consult with the reference archivist about policies and procedures regarding the creation of duplicating master and use copies of the original recordings.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The series is divided into three sections: organizations, conferences, and clippings and miscellaneous. Organizations are arranged alphabetically by title of the organization. Within organization, materials are arranged alphabetically by title of the printed piece. Conferences are arranged chronologically by date of the conference. Within individual conferences, materials are arranged alphabetically by titled of the printed piece. The end of the series contains one folder of clippings and miscellaneous documents.
